ip arrived at\nAlexandria on 22 September with a\ncargo of four 32-ton tanks, sixteen\n16-ton tanks, and about 100 12-ton\ntanks for the Egyptian army.\n\nThe tanks appear to be German World\nWar II models. The unloading of tanks has been con-\nfirmed by the personal observation\n\nDuring the week of 19 September,\ntwo other vessels dis-\ncharged miscellaneous army field equipment, two turbo-\nelectric railway engines for military use, and two heavy\nmobile cranes at Alexandria.\n\nComment\n\nThe addition of 120 tanks would double\nthe number of the Egyptian army's\noperational tanks.\n\nThe country source of these tanks is\nnot known. Egypt has contracts to receive tanks from\nboth Britain and France--but not in this quantity.\n\nEgypt signed a five-year \"open agreement\" with the\nSoviet Union on 21 September and that Cairo's initial or-\nder from the USSR included 100 heavy tanks, as well as\n200 jet aircraft, six torpedo patrol boats, and two sub-\nmarines. This report stated that the first shipment of\nSoviet equipment had been inspected by Egyptian officers\nat Odessa and had already been or was about to be shipped", "token_count": 197, "token_end_0based": 196, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "2 egypt reportedly receives large number of tanks an egyptian-flag ship arrived at alexandria on 22 september with a cargo of four 32-ton tanks sixteen 16-ton tanks and about 100 12-ton tanks for the egyptian army the tanks appear to be german world war ii models the unloading of tanks has been con firmed by the personal observation during the week of 19 september two other vessels dis charged miscellaneous army field equipment two turbo electric railway engines for military use and two heavy mobile cranes at alexandria comment the addition of 120 tanks would double the number of the egyptian army's operational tanks the country source of these tanks is not known egypt has contracts to receive tanks from both britain and france but not in this quantity egypt signed a five-year open agreement with the soviet union on 21 september and that cairo's initial or der from the ussr included 100 heavy tanks as well as 200 jet aircraft six torpedo patrol boats and two sub marines this report stated that the first shipment of soviet equipment had been inspected by egyptian officers at odessa and had already been or was about to be shipped", "unred_source_page": 5}
